<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-80',
    prompt: 'Create a cooking mistake recovery kit by assembling emergency ingredients and practicing 3 disaster recovery techniques: oversalted dish rescue, broken sauce repair, and burnt food salvage',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Having emergency ingredients and practiced recovery techniques transforms kitchen disasters from meal-ruining catastrophes into manageable challenges that build cooking confidence. Stock items like unsalted broth, cream, lemon juice, and fresh herbs for common fixes, then practice deliberate mistakes with simple dishes to master recovery skills. This preparation ensures you can confidently handle cooking emergencies rather than starting over, building the resilience that separates confident cooks from those who panic when things go wrong.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-81',
    prompt: 'Identify and practice fixing 3 specific seasoning mistakes: oversalted soup, underseasoned roasted vegetables, and poorly balanced salad dressing',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Mastering seasoning recovery techniques builds confidence and transforms cooking mistakes into learning opportunities rather than ruined meals. Practice diluting oversalted soup with unsalted stock or cream, rescue bland vegetables with finishing salt and fresh herbs, and balance acidic or oily dressings by adjusting vinegar, oil, and seasoning ratios. These fundamental correction skills teach you that most seasoning problems are fixable and develop the palate sensitivity essential for confident cooking.'
  }
];</parameter>
